entities.name: RowType
entities.description: A type representing an array of objects with string keys and any type of values.

entities.name: database
entities.description: A generic representation of a database interface.

entities.name: TableName
entities.description: A type representing the name of a table within a database.

entities.name: TableSchema
entities.description: A type representing the schema of a database table, which can vary in structure.

entities.name: table
entities.description: A representation of a specific table within a database, used for various table operations.

relationships.description: The database query returns a RowType.
The database uses a table for various operations such as create, drop, truncate, rename, and insert.
The table has a type of TableName for specifying the table name.
The table has a type of TableSchema for specifying the table schema.
